sentence: Technology stocks still were edging higher in Thursday morning trading, with shares of tech companies in the S&P 500 posting a 0.1% gain.

In company news, shares of The KEYW Holding Corp ( KEYW ) rallied Thursday after the software firm beats Wall Street expectations with its Q4 financial results, prompting at least one analyst upgrade this morning.
The company reported a net loss of $0.12 per share during the three months ended Dec. 31, or $0.06 narrower than the Capital IQ consensus expecting an $0.18 per share loss.
Revenue climbed 9.6% over last year to $80.7 million, also topping the $75.96 million consensus.
Following the better-than-expected results, analysts at Chardan Capital Markets raised their investment call for the company's stock to Buy from Neutral, also setting an $8.50 price target.
Separately, the company last night also announced plans to sell its systems engineering and technical assistance business to Quantech Services for $12 million in cash.
The deal is expected to close within the next two weeks.
KEYW shares were up more than 36% at $6.32 each, staying within 16 cents of their session high.
